Package: chartr
Type: Package
Title: Charting economic variables
Version: 0.1
Date: 2016-03-14
Author: Joshua Packwood, Bryan Chen
Maintainer: Joshua Packwood <joshua.packwood@lucusadvisors.com>
Description: chartr is a package for R aimed at making charts with detailed annotations of economic variables. chartr will largely consist of "wrapper" / "convenience" functions utilizing the functions from active R packages such as magrittr, quantmod, and ggplot2.
Imports:
  quantmod,
  xts,
  ggplot2,
  grid,
  hash,
  gridExtra,
  zoo,
  scales,
  data.table,
  lubridate,
  plyr,
  reshape2
License: GPL v.2
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1.9000
